sql:
SELECT name, start_date
FROM interventions
ORDER BY start_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
Significant interventions are those with the lowest p-values; 
P-values represent the probability of obtaining the results of the study, or more extreme, if the null hypothesis is true; 
A lower p-value indicates stronger evidence in favor of the alternative hypothesis, which suggests that the intervention has a significant effect.

* The query assumes that the "impactful interventions" are those with the largest effect sizes; 
* Projected cases, hospitalizations, and deaths are calculated based on the population size and percentage of each demographic group; 
* The results are ordered by report date, age group, vaccination status, and ethnicity description to provide a clear overview of the trends and patterns in the data.
